President Obama will meet with President Xi Jinping of China on June 7-8 at Sunnylands in California. This will be their first meeting since Xi became China's President. They will discuss various topics including bilateral, regional, and global issues. They will also review the progress and challenges in US-China relations over the past four years and explore ways to enhance cooperation while managing their differences. National Security Advisor Tom Donilon will travel to Beijing beforehand to prepare for the meeting.